name: Braun T 1000 Radio
description: A screenprint of the iconic T 1000 shortwave radio was produced to coincide with the Dieter Rams retrospective at the Design Museum. The original edition was limited to a run of 100 – however we have 5 file copies available. The poster is beautifully screenprinted on a black heavy gauge cartridge stock using metallic ink and varnish to simulate the product materials. name: 72: Otl Aicher (catalogue)
description: Catalogue to celebrate and document the exhibition '72: Otl Aicher and the Munich Olympiad' exhibition held in 2007 at Vitsoe's London showroom. Originally part of a special German design edition of Japanese graphic design magazine, Idea. The catalogue acts as a supplement to the exhibition that featured Bibliothèque's extensive collection of design by Aicher's team – including posters, booklets, tickets, mascots, souvenirs and guidelines. Texts are in English and Japanese and feature contributions by the designers Michael Burke and Ian Mclaren – original members of the 72 design team. name: Long Lunch
description: A two colour poster for Bibliothèque's "Long Lunch" talk at The Design Museum. The poster is dual-purpose insofar as it is promoting two events at two venues. This informed the design solution as we used each colour to correspond with each event location (red for the English venue and blue for the Scottish venue). The finished poster could then be displayed in two orientations depending on which lecture it was promoting. name: Cold War Modern 1945–1970
description: Promotional booklet to document our graphic design for Cold War Modern – the first exhibition to examine contemporary design, architecture, film and popular culture on both sides of the Iron Curtain during the Cold War era. The exhibition brought together over 300 exhibits - from a Sputnik and an Apollo mission space suit to films by Stanley Kubrick, paintings by Robert Rauschenberg and Gerhard Richter, fashion by Paco Rabanne, products by Charles and Ray Eames and Dieter Rams and architecture by Le Corbusier, Richard Buckminster Fuller and Archigram. Format: 210 x 280mm, 24pp, self cover + tip-in Print: CMYK Stock: coated white plus uncoated grey tip-in Binding: black saddle stitch More here – Cold War Modern OVERSEAS ORDERS: As delivery costs vary depending on the size and destination please contact us for a quote at shop@bibliothequeeditions.com Please enquire if you are interested in purchasing any of the items on the Bibliothèque website.
